messages.messageBody:
Life is interesting that way. I'm a female born under all male signs. The males I've met with the same or close birthdays are always surprised when I can tell them all about themselves after just meeting them. It helps that I have an older brother born just a few days after me maybe. Two of my siblings were born two days apart at a different time of the year and they shared similar personalities. Any who, if you believe a God can create the universe we live in, then it makes sense that the rest of it lines up.

Vicki who does see the argument between creationism and evolution as being much of a debate.



----- Original Message ----
From: Laura Beaudin <laura.beaudin@...>

Subject: [unschoolingbasics] OT strange occurrences WAS:Confessions of a 'do it nower', was Not being boring ... How?


That reminded me of another eerie situation. I'm on a list for
diabetics and was always conversing with this one lady. Well, it
turns out that not only do we live in the same city, but we live in
the same building! We moved upstairs from a 1-bedroom to a
two-bedroom apartment and I mentioned that. She put two and two
together, LOL. Even stranger is that we were born only a few days apart.

Laura

At 11:17 AM 26/09/2008, you wrote:

>There are no less than four Melissa Grays in our town alone! I only
>know that because at the library and pharmacy our things get mixed up
>all the time. One of them even has my birthday, in a different year.
>Eerie, yes?
>
>Thanks for the congrats. We're excited and a little taken back. But
>that's a LONG story.
>Melissa
